Reasoning: The paper discusses the challenges involved in developing a smartphone app to extract behavioural markers of mental health from passive sensor data. This involves technical challenges related to sensor data collection and analysis, as well as issues related to the acceptability of passive data collection for mental health research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), which deals with the design, evaluation, and implementation of interactive computing systems for human use. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical implications of computing technologies, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with the analysis and modeling of social networks, cs.OH (Other Computer Science), which covers interdisciplinary topics related to computer science, and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), which deals with the security and privacy of computing systems.
